<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Portfolio</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
    <script type="module" defer src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/gh/imananoosheh/github-contributions-fetch@latest/github_calendar_widget.js"></script>
</head>
<body> 
    <section id="home">
        <img id="jprof" src="/images/cat.jpg" alt="Profile Picture">
        <h1>Juan Antony Tarigan</h1>
    </section>
    
    <section id="about">
        <h2>About Me</h2>
        <p id="aboutText"><%- aboutJuan %></p>
        <% if (!admin1 && admin2)  { %>
            <form action="/portfolio/update/juan" method="POST" id="editForm" style="display: none;">
                <textarea name="aboutText" rows="10" cols="50"><%= aboutJuan %></textarea>
                <button type="submit">Save</button>
            </form>
            <button onclick="toggleEdit()">Edit</button>
        <% } %>
    </section>
    
    <section id="projects">
        <div id="projectList">
        <h2>My Projects</h2>
            <h3>BChat</h3>
            <img src="/images/bchat.png" alt="Project 1">
            <p>BChat is an online media social platform that is made for BCIT students focusing on communication feature like chatting but also include features like uploading content and profile.
            I worked on developing the chatting feature between students using socket.io and also responsible for the frontend of the chatting page. Using the database, I also implemented a sidebar for chatting history where all the previous chat with other students are shown and can be accessed</p>

            <h3>PHSA</h3>
            <img src="/images/phsa.jpeg" alt="Project 2">
            <p>Provincial Health Services Authority is a health authority that provides specialized health care services, supports health professionals, and manages health care resources across the province. My team was assigned a project from PHSA to create a website with several features. I worked on creating a chatbot using OpenAI API to assist preceptors with their evalution of students their currently responsible for.</p>
            <% if (!admin1 && admin2)  { %>   
                <button id="addProjectButton" onclick="addProject()">Add Project</button>
            <% } %>
        </div>

    </section>
    
    <section id="github">
        <h2>GitHub Contributions</h2>
        <div id="calendar-component" username="KyouuT" theme-color="#333333" background-color="#fff"></div>
            <div id="github-contributions"></div>
            <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/github-contributions-widget@latest/dist/github-contributions-widget.min.js"></script>
            <script>
                new GitHubCalendar("#github-contributions", "your-github-username");
            </script>
        <p>Check out my GitHub profile for more contributions: <a href="https://github.com/KyouuT" target="_blank">GitHub Profile</a></p>
    </section>

    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
<script>
    function toggleEdit() {
        const aboutText = document.getElementById('aboutText');
        const editForm = document.getElementById('editForm');
        if (editForm.style.display === 'none') {
            aboutText.style.display = 'none';
            editForm.style.display = 'block';
        } else {
            aboutText.style.display = 'block';
            editForm.style.display = 'none';
        }
    }

    function addProject() {
        // Prompt the user for title and description
        const title = prompt("Enter the project title:");
        if (!title) {
            alert("Title cannot be empty!");
            return;
        }

        const description = prompt("Enter the project description:");
        if (!description) {
            alert("Description cannot be empty!");
            return;
        }

        // Get the project list container
        const projectList = document.getElementById('projectList');

        // Create new h3 and p elements
        const newTitle = document.createElement('h3');
        newTitle.textContent = title;

        const newDescription = document.createElement('p');
        newDescription.textContent = description;

        // Append the new elements to the project list
        projectList.appendChild(newTitle);
        projectList.appendChild(newDescription);
    }
</script>
</html>


 
